    "summary": "I graduated in experimental psychology (Tilburg), did some programming work, followed a second study in Cognitive Artificial Intelligence (Utrecht), obtained my Ph.D. on a project concerning aesthetics of textures (Groningen). I worked as a postdoc in psychology departments in Giessen and Nijmegen, working on the perception of materials and on aesthetics and a few other topics. From 2018 to 2022 I was a visiting professor in Santo Andr\u00e9, Brazil, where I taught various courses concerning Cognitive Psychology and Statistics. I also set up various courses, about neuro-aesthetics and attention and consciousness. Back in the Netherlands I prepare myself for data analyst/data scientist roles.\n\nIn my spare time I like to read informative books of all kinds (psychology, neuroscience, biology, history, politics, economy, physics, chemistry). Other hobbies vary a bit. In Brazil I learned to appreciate nature and to go bird-watching. Before that, I liked to visit historic places and cultural events, which I still do now and then. I also like listening to popular music. Visiting concerts or music festivals is still fun.",
